ionic liquids as lubricants','2015-03-18 13:05:00.000000'),(87675,88509,'PEOPLE-2007-4-1.IOF','Hydrogen and fuel cells (combining hydrogen and oxygen to produce electricity) are excellent candidates for clean energy production. However, hydrogen is primarily produced by reforming crude oil, coal, natural gas and organic waste, a process that results in high carbon monoxide (CO) content that degrades fuel cell performance.','Making your electric car more efficient','2015-06-29 18:15:00.000000'),(87676,91259,'INFRA-2008-1.1.1','European physics research requires shared national facilities. An EU project united one set of similar installations, promoting collective access, joint research and networking opportunities, yielding a substantial research output.','Sharing tools for light research','2014-12-08 17:40:00.000000'),(87677,88483,'PEOPLE-2007-4-2.IIF','Biodiversity loss is one of the primary concerns of ecologists globally. A study of a region in Trinidad has revealed both conflicts and common interests in ecosystem preservation.','Maintaining biodiversity in a tourist paradise','2015-06-29 18:14:00.000000'),(87678,89855,'PEOPLE-2007-2-2.ERG','With the explosion of Web-based information, there is an ever-increasing need for methods that more quickly and accurately help users get the information they want and need. An EU-funded initiative has resulted in innovative advances in data collection techniques for use in Web searches, social networking and data mining for automated Web marketing, among other applications.','Untangling the Web','2015-06-29 18:13:00.000000'),(87679,91126,'ENV.2008.3.1.1.2.;NMP-2008-1.2-2','Access to clean drinking water is necessary for life. Yet, the availability of safe fresh water supplies is shrinking due to a growing amount of hazardous chemicals contaminating our water. European Union (EU) funded scientists have developed highly effective catalytic water purification technology to reverse this worrying trend.','Microscopic labyrinths for selective water purification','2015-06-30 05:22:00.000000'),(87680,90158,'FP7-PEOPLE-IRSES-2008','Novel devices are often founded on the innovative properties of the materials used to make them. The environmental and health communities can expect important advances thanks to new nanocomposites produced with EU support.','New materials for environmental and biological applications','2015-06-30 08:59:00.000000'),(87681,90482,'FP7-PEOPLE-IEF-2008','Photonic crystals are composed of nanostructures that affect propagation of electromagnetic (EM) waves (think of the traditional prism and its ability to separate the light in the visible spectrum). An EU-funded initiative has shed light, so to speak, on new methods of optical signal processing with far-reaching applications.','Making the optical signal ï¿½crystal clearï¿½','2015-06-29 18:13:00.000000'),(87683,92754,'FP7-PEOPLE-IEF-2008','Many of us have marvelled at the beauty and technological know-how behind arched bridges. European researchers have made an important contribution to the design and construction of steel arches which, until now, did not take into account their inherent curvature.','Why curved is not the same as straight','2015-06-29 18:11:00.000000'),(87687,90618,'FP7-PEOPLE-IIF-2008','Security has become a global issue and an increasing concern. EU-funded researchers have developed a highly accurate and potentially low-cost tracking device to address the barrage of cheap and unreliable imaging devices that have flooded the market in the last decade.','A portable radar for accurately detecting danger','2015-06-29 18:05:00.000000'),(87689,90790,'PEOPLE-2007-4-3.IRG','Cancer stem cells reside in a microenvironment, a niche, which always contains blood vessels. The VNTME-GAVARD project studied the functional interaction between cancer stem cells and endothelial cells of the vasculature.','Vascular niche of cancer stem cells','2015-06-30 09:18:00.000000'),(87703,89391,'SEC-2007-2.3-01','New surveillance systems can help boost security measures by matching unattended baggage quickly and easily.','Putting an end to lost baggage','2015-09-18 13:42:00.000000'),(87708,89839,'PEOPLE-2007-2-2.ERG','Matrices and specifically defined operators that act on them are critical to defining and understanding problems in numerous fields in the natural and engineering sciences. An EU-funded initiative developed innovative mathematical techniques to help solve the infinite matrix problem.','Spectral theory and solving infinite matrices','2015-06-29 18:13:00.000000'),(87710,92393,'PEOPLE-2007-2-2.ERG','Bone tissue regeneration is an active field of research with applicability to the nearly 75 million people worldwide suffering from bone disease and musculoskeletal disorders. An EU-funded initiative has led to the development of new biomaterials promising enhanced new bone formation as well as improved oxygenation and blood supply to the new tissue for sustained function.','Better scaffolds for building new bones','2015-06-29 18:13:00.000000'),(87712,91227,'FP7-PEOPLE-IEF-2008','Communication between cells in the brain involves glutamate receptors. European scientists dissected the mechanism that controls proper localisation of glutamate receptors in the hippocampus.','Signals and receptors guiding brain function','2015-06-29 18:12:00.000000'),(87713,87833,'HEALTH-2007-2.3.2-6','A European consortium is tackling HIV infection by generating neutralising antibodies. This is expected to act as a preventive vaccine blocking entry of the virus into the cell.','Towards a preventive HIV vaccine','2015-06-29 18:11:00.000000'),(87716,90377,'FP7-PEOPLE-IEF-2008','An EU-funded project has focused efforts on studying the zebrafish in order to improve our understanding of the mechanisms behind appropriate sensory organ functioning.','Making sense of the zebrafish\'s senses','2015-06-29 18:11:00.000000'),(87718,90662,'FP7-PEOPLE-IEF-2008','All living cells are surrounded by a plasma membrane that separates their internal from their external environments and controls what goes in and out. EU researchers have combined nanotechnology and genetics to enhance the way the cell membrane constituents harvest light from the sun, with applications in agriculture, energy and medicine.','Building light harvesters on cell membranes','2015-06-29 18:10:00.000000'),(87721,90631,'PEOPLE-2007-4-3.IRG','Magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) has been the tool of choice in diagnosis of brain lesions related to abnormal blood supply (cerebrovascular disease, or CVD). An EU-funded project is seeking to improve conventional MRI-based methods of CVD detection such that they are less dependent on human expert-based interpretation.','Advanced imaging techniques for detecting pathology','2015-06-29 18:10:00.000000'),(87722,90499,'PEOPLE-2007-4-3.IRG','Haptic is taken from a Greek word meaning to touch that, and in its plural form refers to the science of the sense of touch. From this science has come technology, where haptic is used as an adjective when referring to systems that rely on minute changes in pressure or force to produce a response ï¿½ witness touch-screen displays.','High precision remote-controlled robotics','2015-08-12 15:10:00.000000'),(87723,95725,'FP7-PEOPLE-2009-IOF','When we say we did a job really fast, weï¿½re generally talking about an order of minutes to even hours. In contrast, ultrafast processes in biology, chemistry and physics are events that occur in the femtosecond (fsec) range, where one fsec is equivalent to one quadrillionth of a second.','Keeping up with ultrafast subatomic interactions','2015-06-29 18:09:00.000000'),(87725,90727,'FP7-PEOPLE-IEF-2008','A group of researchers made a major discovery that supports the hypothesis linking disturbances in circadian rhythms and the advent of metabolic disorders. This is important for the prevention and treatment of conditions such as obesity and diabetes mellitus.','Loss of sleep interferes with our metabolism','2015-06-29 18:08:00.000000'),(87729,87294,'PEOPLE-2007-4-1.IOF','Recent advances in scanning probe microscopy (SPM) have enabled investigation of a number of processes at the single molecule level. In addition to biological importance such as understanding DNA-enzyme reactions, single molecule interactions are of interest for studying and developing new electrical behaviours at the single molecule level with potential relevance to the electronics industry.','Studying conductivity at the single molecule level','2015-06-29 18:08:00.000000'),(87731,90775,'PEOPLE-2007-2-1.IEF','A study of arctic biodiversity has advanced understanding of the biology of plants in arctic environments as well as of the adaptation role played by their endophytic bacteria.','What can bacteria from sub-zero environments teach us?','2015-06-29 18:07:00.000000'),(87736,90657,'FP7-PEOPLE-IIF-2008','Telomeres are repetitive sequences of DNA at the end of chromosomes that protect our genetic information from certain harmful interactions. In this way, they have been likened to the plastic tips on shoelaces.','Fighting cancer at the chromosome level','2015-06-29 18:06:00.000000'),(87738,90396,'FP7-PEOPLE-IEF-2008','Research into the genomics of tyrosine kinases has shed more light on the evolutionary development of the single cell to the complexity of the multicellular animal and plant.','Evolving from a single cell to the multicellular','2015-06-29 18:04:00.000000'),(87739,90559,'FP7-PEOPLE-IEF-2008','Dendritic cells (DCs) play an important role in the function of the mammalian immune system. European researchers have identified and characterised a novel type of skin DC and thus provided insight for new immune system-based therapies and more effective vaccines.','Stimulating an immune response','2015-06-29 18:04:00.000000'),(87740,90425,'FP7-PEOPLE-IEF-2008','Cellular mitosis is the process by which cells divide. It is critical to everyday tissue renewal and repair and is also involved in the uncontrolled cell division seen in cancer.','Understanding cell division','2015-06-29 18:04:00.000000'),(87741,92943,'FP7-PEOPLE-IEF-2008','New online search technology and algorithms are set to help users more easily find what they want in the growing sea of online multimedia content.','Multimedia at your fingertips','2015-06-29 18:04:00.000000'),(87742,90520,'FP7-PEOPLE-IEF-2008','The integration of energy and resource conservation to enable sustainable high-performance manufacturing of advanced materials is of fundamental importance to both the efficiency of manufacturers as well as to the environment. EU researchers have evaluated three different factors in the manufacturing process with respect to the above to provide recommendations for improved sustainable manufacturing.','More competitive companies and a healthier planet','2015-06-29 18:04:00.000000'),(87743,90142,'FP7-PEOPLE-IAPP-2008','The rise in obesity and its medical consequences are a serious public health concern throughout Europe. An EU-funded project explored the factors that influence obesity and some technologies to help families lead healthier lifestyles.','How technology can promote healthy living','2015-01-19 10:36:00.000000'),(87744,90137,'FP7-PEOPLE-IRSES-2008','Various types of engineered wood and structural timbers offer a sustainable, low-cost, versatile and convenient alternative to conventional building materials. An EU-funded project imported and adapted the latest techniques from New Zealand, a global leader in the field.','Wood, the best building solution','2015-06-29 18:03:00.000000'),(87745,92966,'FP7-PEOPLE-IRSES-2008','A team of scientists is advancing studies in the use of biomimetic materials for application in devices tailored for ensuring and monitoring food safety. Inspired by nature, project efforts promise to offer widespread benefits for humans.','Making good sense of nature\'s offerings','2015-06-29 18:03:00.000000'),(87746,90630,'PEOPLE-2007-4-3.IRG','Wireless sensor networks (WS