n activity and central nervous system development in newborn babies. One of the many applications promises to be new therapies for epilepsy.','Food for thought in the developing brain','2015-06-29 18:05:00.000000'),(88446,88216,'HEALTH-2007-2.4.2-1','Understanding how atherosclerotic plaques form would certainly help in the development of new therapies against cardiovascular disease. In this context, a large European consortium looked at the role of inflammation in atherosclerosis development.','Targeting atherosclerosis','2015-01-19 11:49:00.000000'),(88447,86774,'HEALTH-2007-2.2.2-2','Ageing can be accompanied by impaired non-regenerative fibroproliferative tissue healing and chronic inflammation resulting in loss of organ function. EU-funded researchers sought to elucidate the underlying mechanisms involved in this process.','Abnormal wound healing mechanisms','2015-01-19 11:50:00.000000'),(88449,88196,'HEALTH-2007-2.3.2-3','European researchers are developing new assays to detect drug resistant strains of Mycobacterium tuberculosis.','Improving detection of drug-resistant tuberculosis','2015-06-29 16:37:00.000000'),(88472,88892,'PEOPLE-2007-1-1-ITN','A European integrated project addressed the clinical need for diagnosis and treatment of fungal infections. European scientists developed new leads for anti-fungal vaccines, drugs and diagnostic markers.','A new era in fungal infection treatment','2015-03-18 13:09:00.000000'),(88473,88815,'PEOPLE-2007-1-1-ITN','The use of several mathematical techniques has improved the capabilities of computer-aided design. A trained network of mainly early stage researchers is now proficient in the improved technology, which will benefit industry as well as academic research.','Computer aided design improved by mathematics','2014-11-13 12:15:00.000000'),(88474,88903,'PEOPLE-2007-1-1-ITN','An EU training initiative is answering key questions on the role of host-gut microbiota cross-talk in the development and maintenance of a healthy gut.','Towards maintaining a healthy gut','2015-06-29 21:07:00.000000'),(88475,89014,'PEOPLE-2007-1-1-ITN','Notch signalling is a highly conserved pathway that plays a key role in cell-fate determination and differentiation of various cell types. European scientists have teamed up to delineate the Notch pathway and find its association with disease.','Unravelling the role of Notch signalling in disease','2015-06-29 21:06:00.000000'),(88476,88974,'PEOPLE-2007-1-1-ITN','The field of nanomaterial construction is rapidly expanding with numerous novel applications. To increase the existing pool with new candidates, European researchers looked closely at the process of nanomaterial generation.','Towards novel nanomaterials','2014-12-08 17:44:00.000000'),(88477,90717,'PEOPLE-2007-2-3.COFUND','The Spanish capital has taken important steps to attract young researchers from around the world. From energy to nanoscience, the city has demonstrated its role as an academic and research-oriented destination of choice.','Madrid becomes top researcher hotspot','2015-10-06 16:13:00.000000'),(88479,90622,'PEOPLE-2007-2-3.COFUND','A targeted training programme should help stem the EU brain drain. The initiative is being designed to invest in career development for future science leaders.','Training future science leaders','2015-06-30 10:36:00.000000'),(88480,90827,'PEOPLE-2007-2-3.COFUND','Recruiting Irish scientists in a three-year research scheme has helped to improve the competitiveness of Ireland\'s scientific community and its research potential on a global scale.','In support of scientific research in Ireland','2015-04-23 13:01:00.000000'),(88482,87328,'PEOPLE-2007-3-1-IAPP','A European initiative is improving ultrasound imaging analysis by developing tools that facilitate multi-planar views of the organ and two-dimensional (2D) plus time movies. Such techniques are expected to increase diagnosis precision and will open up new imaging applications.','Novel ultrasound tools improve diagnostic imaging','2015-06-29 21:05:00.000000'),(88483,91491,'PEOPLE-2007-2-1.IEF','The concept of unified legal discourse, or legal discursivity, has been an elusive one for European thinkers. One projectï¿½s new approach to understanding the issue has shed light on how legal discourse should evolve.','The rocky road to legal discourse','2015-06-29 21:05:00.000000'),(88484,88024,'PEOPLE-2007-2-1.IEF','An 20th century Spanish philosopher who has drawn on contemporary German philosophy and Classical Greek philosophy can help us understand the roots of a true European identity.','Europe\'s identity through philosophy','2015-06-29 21:05:00.000000'),(88485,87729,'PEOPLE-2007-2-1.IEF','It is not easy to measure the well-being of immigrants against their true desires to integrate into their host country. A new approach using a more implicit line of questioning has the potential to clarify the picture.','Better measures for immigrants\' well-being','2015-06-29 21:04:00.000000'),(88493,89685,'PEOPLE-2007-2-1.IEF','An underwater landslide could cause a tsunami and wreak havoc on shore. The Mediterranean isn\'t immune to such scenarios, but improved knowledge can help manage them.','Hazards from the deep','2015-06-29 20:59:00.000000'),(88494,91488,'PEOPLE-2007-2-1.IEF','Man has often learned from history, and international conflicts are no exception to this rule. A look at an important European example could help civilisation manage its conflicts in a better way.','Old disputes for new solutions','2015-06-29 20:58:00.000000'),(88495,88086,'PEOPLE-2007-2-1.IEF','An EU-funded initiative has offered a first step towards better understanding the development of a European consciousness. Research and activities followed a historical and comparative perspective to provide more insight into differing views of Eurocentrism.','Delving into the construction of European consciousness','2015-06-29 21:42:00.000000'),(88497,88126,'PEOPLE-2007-2-1.IEF','Research has been conducted into the influence of Europe on Latin American visitors on their return to their home countries and contribution to nation building between the interwar years.','European influence on Latin American nation-building','2015-06-29 21:39:00.000000'),(88498,90586,'FP7-PEOPLE-IIF-2008','As technology and knowledge advance, so do consumer products and companies looking to benefit from new markets. This has raised a debate in the healthcare arena in relation to direct-to-consumer (DTC) genetic testing, a service that changes and bypasses the traditional patient-doctor relationship.','Direct-to-consumer genetic testing effects on healthcare','2015-06-29 21:38:00.000000'),(88500,90216,'FP7-PEOPLE-IAPP-2008','The public sector has often been slow to embrace change and technology, resulting in underperforming services for citizens. An EU initiative developed a model measuring citizen satisfaction of e-government services to enable government structures to improve on citizen offerings.','Optimising e-government services for citizens','2015-05-25 17:50:00.000000'),(88501,92109,'FP7-PEOPLE-IIF-2008','End-to-end design of wireless multimedia systems poses a number of challenges that calls for heightened research and transfer of both expertise and knowledge. One EU-funded initiative has made headway in this area by establishing an international research group focused on providing relevant solutions.','Stepping up the capacity of wireless communication','2015-06-29 21:34:00.000000'),(88505,91815,'FP7-PEOPLE-IEF-2008','An innovative initiative seeking to advance the study and theory of psychological games has contributed to knowledge in the field and spurred collaboration within the related scientific community.','Motivation and reasoning in psychological games','2015-06-29 21:27:00.000000'),(88506,91143,'FP7-PEOPLE-IEF-2008','European research has delved into the role of Egypt in inter-cultural exchanges in the 11th century. The study outlines and compares the different contexts in which various communities regarded Egyptian, Greek and Semitic heroes, philosophers and scholars.','Perceptions of ancient heroes in early medieval societies','2015-06-29 21:27:00.000000'),(88524,86714,'PEOPLE-2007-3-1-IAPP','New antimicrobial compounds are needed as bacteria become resistant to currently available drugs. Addressing this pressing issue, the \'New antimicrobials\' (NAM) project explored new sources and techniques for developing novel antimicrobials and mechanisms behind their actions.','New weapons in the war against microbes','2015-06-30 07:43:00.000000'),(88527,89830,'PEOPLE-2007-4-1.IOF','Development in many organisms uses a restricted set of physical processes to produce functionally and morphologically diverse features. How the dynamics of development have evolved to shape these phenotypes is yet to be determined.','The evolution of development','2015-06-17 12:40:00.000000'),(88528,88372,'PEOPLE-2007-4-2.IIF','European scientists provided an innovative model of neurons which is expected to revolutionise neurochemistry and aid the study of electrochemical signal transmission.','Mimicking neurons','2015-06-29 21:03:00.000000'),(88565,90266,'PEOPLE-2007-4-3.IRG','European researchers are using electrophysiological and neuroimaging techniques to characterise brain activity in the sleeping schizophrenic brain.','Importance of sleep spindles in schizophrenia','2015-06-29 21:01:00.000000'),(88567,90877,'PEOPLE-2007-4-2.IIF','European scientists are investigating the genetics of a phytoplankton that acts as a carbon sink and produces a climate-active gas. Unravelling what genes are responsible for survival of the sexual phase promises to unlock the secret of repopulation and formation of new blooms.','A microscopic alga with a big agenda','2015-06-29 21:00:00.000000'),(88568,88053,'PEOPLE-2007-2-1.IEF','Inserting probes deep into the brain for prosthesis stimulation and research presents many challenges. A European team has developed a novel neuroprobe that 