en established to oversee a range of projects aiming to reduce cosmetic testing on animals.','Towards animal-free cosmetic testing','2015-02-09 16:14:00.000000'),(90420,97237,'AAT.2010.4.1-8.','Reducing production costs and enhancing sustainability and performance are key goals of the aerospace sector. Novel casting technology developed with EU support will enable improved manufacture of titanium (Ti)-based components to address all three.','Aircraft casting overcomes reactivity','2015-01-19 17:17:00.000000'),(90421,96282,'INFRA-2010-1.1.27','An EU-funded project is developing and providing access to a range of tools and services for earthquake prediction and hazard prevention.','New earthquake monitoring services','2015-01-19 17:17:00.000000'),(90422,98535,'INFRA-2010-3.2','Training workshops and a new handbook have given managers and civil servants in Europe the necessary tools and know-how to streamline how research infrastructures (RIs) are managed.','Better management of research infrastructures','2014-11-14 12:09:00.000000'),(90423,97885,'HEALTH.2010.2.4.4-2','Up to 30 million Europeans suffer from a staggeringly long list of various rare diseases. Because the patients of each of the 6ï¿½000ï¿½8ï¿½000 disorders are sparsely scattered across the EU, the region must combine research resources towards finding new therapies.','Working together on rare disease research','2015-06-30 03:45:00.000000'),(90424,96835,'SPA.2010.1.1-04','A recent project has developed forest monitoring tools and skills in several developing countries found within tropical climates.','Improving tropical forest monitoring','2015-08-03 10:27:00.000000'),(90425,97132,'INFRA-2010-2.2.8','An EU-funded project is ensuring that the region has the capacity to deal with highly infectious micro-organisms in research laboratories. It will also coordinate international research activities to make sure that funding is spent efficiently in the search for diagnostics and therapies.','Coordinating dangero