odelling in coronary artery disease (CAD) should help physicians make a more informed diagnostic decision.','Remodelling in coronary artery disease','2015-09-15 12:29:00.000000'),(91262,92804,'SiS-2009-1.3.2.1','EU-funded scientists optimised a European framework called MasterPlan for ethical and safe conduct in nanoscience research. A tool called Codemeter was developed to assist in spreading awareness and better implementation of the European Commission code of conduct (EC-CoC) with regard to nanoscience research.','Conducting nanotechnology research responsibly','2015-06-30 05:52:00.000000'),(91263,94432,'Fission-2009-2.3.1','An EU-funded project has been developing and applying new computational and experimental methodologies for studying the thermal-hydraulics phenomena involved in next-generation reactors.','New tools for nuclear reactors','2015-07-21 18:12:00.000000'),(91264,88227,'HEALTH-2007-1.4-3','Most food allergies are chronic lifelong diseases affecting around 10 million Europeans. A curative treatment for food allergies is the only way to alleviate these potentially life-threatening conditions.','Treatment for food allergy','2015-03-31 14:45:00.000000'),(91265,109305,'REGIONS-1;REGIONS-2009-1','Protection of coasts and estuaries is of particular concern to local, national and international policymakers as populations and their demands on natural systems increase. An EU-funded initiative has focused on the problem to develop a series of sustainable solutions.','Conserving Europe\'s coastal waters','2014-11-17 10:23:00.000000'),(91266,94426,'KBBE-2009-1-4-03','Meeting future food demands will put pressure on producers and distributors. A new information system ensures they can face up to the challenges.','Meeting the food challenge','2015-06-30 09:09:00.000000'),(91268,92734,'NMP-2008-4.0-4','Advanced fibre lasers have numerous advantages over conventional lasers including better efficiency and beam quality at a lower cost. The latest systems developed 