haracterised by skin blistering with no treatment available. The gene therapy treatment of this genetic disorder is being tested by a European research consortium.','Gene therapy strategy to heal skin disease','2015-07-21 18:19:00.000000'),(91582,98539,'HEALTH.2010.3.4-3','An EU-funded support programme has provided training and skills development for a number of African epidemiology researchers.','Building research capacity in Africa','2015-05-08 17:22:00.000000'),(91583,98971,'NMP-2010-1.2-3','New thermoelectric materials could help to harvest heat lost by trucks, aircraft and factories. A material\'s initial composition, the processing techniques, the structures formed and final properties of the material are important.','Energy from waste heat','2014-11-17 15:17:00.000000'),(91584,97702,'HEALTH.2010.3.4-6','India is using pro-poor demand-side financing interventions to reduce maternal mortality through better access to emergency obstetric care (EmOC). EU-funded researchers are evaluating the efficacy of such large-scale interventions.','Pro-poor Indian maternity programmes','2015-05-14 11:18:00.000000'),(91585,103818,'JTI-CS-2011-1-GRC-05-005','In the near future, aircraft combining helicopter manouvrability and conventional aircraft speed and range will allow passengers to take off and land in tight places, using tilting rotors and a fixed wing. A virtual simulator of the full-scale piloted vehicle and air traffic control (ATC) scenario is supporting the effort.','Fast Rotorcraft on the horizon','2015-05-19 11:44:00.000000'),(91586,97380,'ENV.2010.4.2.2-1','Researchers in Europe are working to fill in the remaining gaps in the international standard for environmental economic accounting. An EU initiative has harmonised accounts for the environment to better inform decision making and policymaking.','Honing environmental and economic accounting principles','2015-09-28 12:19:00.000000'),(91587,99560,'AAT.2011.7-18.','Tomorrow\'s freight planes will have to better