strogens in ovarian cancer','2015-06-30 07:37:00.000000'),(91802,102532,'HEALTH-2011.2.2.1-2','Neurodegenerative diseases (NDs) represent a major health care problem, with current treatments addressing the symptoms rather than the cause. Identifying novel therapeutic targets of neuroinflammation will target multiple NDs as sustained inflammation is responsible for progressive neurodegeneration.','Searching for novel therapeutic targets','2015-02-24 18:00:00.000000'),(91803,100047,'AAT.2011.4.4-3.','An EU initiative is developing intelligent design techniques that can seamlessly change the shape of an aircraft\'s wings. This technology has the potential to reduce development time and costs in manufacturing.','Lowering air travel costs thanks to smart materials','2015-09-30 10:28:00.000000'),(91810,96164,'SiS','Providing opportunities for meaningful scientific exchange and the advancement of research can boost the potential of brilliant young minds. In this vein, a European project was conceived to support the 60th meeting of Nobel Laureates.','Nobel Laureates eager to inspire young researchers','2015-06-30 05:14:00.000000'),(91812,90976,'KBBE-2008-2-3-02','Sulphur dioxide (SO2) is traditionally used as an antioxidant and preservative in fruit and vegetable products, dried fruits, snack products and wine. However, SO2 and sulphites strongly reduce vitamin B1 uptake and can present risks to asthma sufferers.','Dispensing with sulphur dioxide in food','2015-06-30 07:35:00.000000'),(91813,102631,'INCO.2011-6.2','Each year, Jordan\'s King Hussein Cancer Centre (KHCC) treats more than 3ï¿½500 new adult and paediatric cancer patients. The EU-funded KHCCBIO project has helped the Centre with its plans to establish a state-of-the-art biospecimen repository for use in cancer research.','Cancer biobank for Jordan','2015-05-08 17:24:00.000000'),(91815,98244,'FP7-PEOPLE-2009-RG','An EU-funded research project is endeavouring to identify how dopamine neurotransmission in specific 