00'),(147194,100964,'SME-2011-1','Keeping a sewerage system clean and functional is crucially important for public health and proper functioning of a city\'s infrastructure. Researchers have developed an automated sewerage inspection and cleaning device that will save time and money.','New automated sewer cleaning system','2015-06-08 12:29:00.000000'),(147195,101125,'SME-2011-1','Monitoring intracranial dynamic pressure (ICP) has the potential to help patients with dementia, chronic headache and other brain-based disorders. This EU-funded project worked on a prototype for a portable, non-invasive device.','Monitoring intracranial dynamic pressure','2015-01-20 14:33:00.000000'),(147196,100189,'SME-2011-1','European scientists have developed a new manufacturing process for photovoltaic (PV) technology, which improves their efficiency and dramatically reduces water usage by the solar cell industry.','Greener and cheaper photovoltaics','2014-11-11 12:05:00.000000'),(147197,100967,'SME-2011-1','Extruded aluminium (Al) accounts for more than half of all Al products in Europe. Enhancing the energy efficiency of processing should have major impact on industry competitiveness and global climate change.','Efficient cooling of extruded Aluminium','2014-10-27 15:28:00.000000'),(147198,100826,'SME-2011-1','The best production methods for aerospace parts with complex geometries have typically been slow and expensive. Advanced technology developed with EU support enables cost-effective mass production of such parts, slashing the selling price in half.','High-power melting for fast processing','2015-03-05 17:48:00.000000'),(147199,100889,'SME-2011-1','Virtualisation technologies are extending their reach, entering lately a new, high-volume space: embedded systems. EU-funded scientists are designing an open-source virtualisation framework that will offer flexibility and higher-level capabilities, morphing the embedded device into a new class of system.','Secure embedded virtualisation systems','2014-11-11 12:10:00.000000'),(147200,101299,'SME-2011-1','Glass optics combining both diffractive and refractive components were the stuff of science fiction until now. Scientists with EU support are developing low-cost technology for production of hybrid glass photonics.','EU hybrid diffractive/refractive lenses','2014-10-27 15:39:00.000000'),(147201,100645,'SME-2011-1','The precise geometrical structure of pores in metallic medical implants is critical for integration of the living bone with the surface of the implant. EU-funded scientists are developing the required manufacturing technology.','Optimising porosity in metallic implants','2014-10-27 15:57:00.000000'),(147202,101400,'SME-2011-1','As micro-structuring has proved its ability to improve the tribological behaviour of surfaces, EU-funded scientists focused on laser technology to reduce friction during contact between moving parts of hydraulic pumps.','Structuring low-friction surfaces for hydraulic systems','2015-05-04 15:38:00.000000'),(147203,100646,'SME-2011-1','Cost-effectively using ground-source heat for energy applications will significantly reduce greenhouse gas emissions. EU-funded scientists developed novel technology to efficiently convert heat from vast untapped geothermal resources.','High-efficiency heat pump','2015-01-20 14:34:00.000000'),(147204,101016,'SME-2011-1','EU-funded scientists\' unveiled technology for outdoor electronic signage and message boards with wireless data connection and solar panels.','Novel electronic paper technology','2015-01-20 14:35:00.000000'),(147205,100224,'SME-2011-1','EU-funded scientists developed thermochemical heat storage technology for high temperatures that should work as a viable alternative to the currently used systems. The system holds great promise for savings in primary energy and costs.','Generating heat on demand','2015-04-10 09:48:00.000000'),(147206,100610,'SME-2011-1','An EU-funded project successfully developed a new photovoltaic (PV) ribbon process that allows high-speed and chemical-free production of soft ribbons. This considerably reduces solar cell cracking.','Crack-resistant solar cells','2015-02-12 14:50:00.000000'),(147207,100305,'SME-2011-1','EU-funded scientists developed a laser-based technique to automatically repair defective photovoltaic (PV) cells and wafers. These should be reused to produce custom, low-cost solar modules.','New solar cells made more efficient','2014-12-05 16:26:00.000000'),(147208,100971,'SME-2011-1','A recent EU-funded research project has developed new prototype stoves that release significantly less carbon monoxide and particulate matter than traditional wood-burning stoves.','Wood stoves that don\'t smoke','2015-07-22 15:43:00.000000'),(147209,102139,'SME-2011-1','Recent research has shown that the use of shock waves can speed up the ageing process traditionally used to improve meat texture and flavour. In light of this, scientists are working towards a shock-wave generator prototype for the meat industry.','Shocking new way to age meat','2014-10-27 16:23:00.000000'),(147210,100962,'SME-2011-1','Coatings that conduct electricity historically fall short on ratings of greenness. Innovative eco-friendly alternatives that are also sprayable, transparent and higher performing are ready to blaze a trail to existing and new markets.','A new era of electrically conductive coatings','2014-12-01 15:33:00.000000'),(147211,104281,'JTI-CS-2011-2-SFWA-02-017','The contra-rotating open rotor (CROR) engine employs uncased blades (not enclosed within the engine nacelle) and promises enhanced efficiency. Scientists are tackling the noise issue, made trickier by the open design, to speed up certification.','Less aircraft noise in a low-emissions design','2015-08-04 10:14:00.000000'),(147214,106811,'SME-2012-1','Despite the advantages of glass over other materials for packaging, the glass container industry must reduce product cost and improve mechanical properties to remain competitive. Novel coatings promise to do both.','Cheap, scratch-resistant glass containers','2014-10-27 16:47:00.000000'),(147216,103068,'NMP.2011.1.4-3','EU-funded scientists are developing a revolutionary multi-modal analytical tool to enable simultaneous measurement of numerous nano-object characteristics. It promises a boost to nanotechnology development and to the EU economy.','All-in-one tool for nanomaterial characterisation','2014-10-27 16:56:00.000000'),(147217,104572,'TPT.2012.3-2.','An EU initiative has helped European businesses in the transport sector to embrace innovation, thus enabling the emergence of more efficient and eco-friendly transport solutions.','Enhancing the innovation capacity of transport SMEs','2015-10-01 10:04:00.000000'),(147218,103072,'NMP.2011.1.3-2','Engineered nanoparticles (ENPs) have found a myriad of uses, particularly in the pigment, ink and paint industry. However, there are concerns about the hazards of producing and using ENPs and the potentially detrimental effects on the environment and our health.','Engineering safe nanoparticles','2014-10-27 17:03:00.000000'),(147219,102485,'NMP.2011.1.4-4','Implants have come to revolutionise medical treatment by replacing, supporting or enhancing the activity of biological structures. A European study is working to advance existing options through the use of innovative materials.','Novel technology for medical implants','2014-10-27 17:05:00.000000'),(147220,106021,'SME-2012-1','Bigger cities mean worse building disasters. Fortunately, most victims carry mobile phones, which can help rescuers to locate them.','Finding phones in rubble','2014-10-27 17:08:00.000000'),(147223,105837,'AAT.2012.6.3-1.','Since the middle of the last century, developments related to the \'conquest of space\' have led to the satellite-based Global Positioning System (GPS) of high precision and continuous global coverage. However, an EU-funded project poses the question \'What if GPS isn\'t available?\'.',