anish and Italian terrorists disengage differently','2014-10-20 09:04:00.000000'),(148937,100886,'SME-2011-1','An EU-funded project developed an easy-to-use, affordable and non-destructive testing tool using ultrasound to detect flaws in spot welds in vehicles.','New tool to expose welding defects','2014-10-20 09:14:00.000000'),(148938,94008,'FP7-PEOPLE-2009-RG','Understanding how protease activated receptors (PARs) work during development was the key objective of a European proposal. The generated information has clinical implications especially in terms of drugs specifically targeting this system.','Signalling redundancy during development','2014-10-22 17:35:00.000000'),(148939,96977,'GC-SST.2010.7-6.','The prospect of electric vehicles on European streets is becoming more palpable, thanks to a series of roadmaps that will direct EU funding and encourage competitiveness in the automotive sector.','Green cars a step closer to reality','2014-10-20 09:19:00.000000'),(148941,98220,'FP7-PEOPLE-2010-IEF','EU-funded scientists are designing novel structures embedded in optical fibres that bode well for the development of fibre-optic sensors.','Advanced optical signal processing','2014-10-20 09:30:00.000000'),(148943,97680,'FP7-PEOPLE-2009-IRSES','Nanocapsules ï¿½ for targeted drug delivery to diseased or damaged cells ï¿½  hold promise for the treatment of many conditions that do not respond to conventional drugs.','Cancer targeting using nanocapsules','2014-10-22 17:33:00.000000'),(148944,96418,'FP7-PEOPLE-2009-IEF','A European study followed an innovative approach to understand the basic mechanisms underlying the development of Alzheimerï¿½s disease. The generated information could be utilised to design new strategies for the cure of this pathological condition.','Understanding Alzheimerï¿½s disease','2014-10-22 17:29:00.000000'),(148945,106746,'SPA.2012.2.1-01','Antennas in synthetic aperture radar (SAR) systems are logistical nightmares as they as large structures th