ration focused on device \'skills\'','2015-04-08 10:27:00.000000'),(158592,105582,'SME-2012-2','A new research consortium is promoting an alternative crop for tobacco farmers in the face of difficult economic conditions.','Sweet deal for struggling tobacco farms','2015-04-08 10:38:00.000000'),(158593,103669,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IIF','Researchers have used advanced molecular biology tools to improve phosphorus uptake in a common crop plant called foxtail millet.','On the path to better millet crops','2015-04-08 10:39:00.000000'),(158594,105857,'HEALTH.2012.2.1.1-3','3D imaging of the human body has revolutionised the detection and diagnosis of disease. New statistical methods for automated spatial analysis of hundreds of biomolecules simultaneously could revolutionise biomedical imaging power.','Analysing spatial distribution of biomolecules in 3D','2015-04-08 10:41:00.000000'),(158595,106018,'HEALTH.2012.1.4-4','RNA therapeutics is gaining ground in the treatment of many diseases. European researchers hope to show it could be a valid intervention for the treatment of Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD).','A novel therapy for muscular dystrophy','2015-04-08 10:43:00.000000'),(158596,105497,'NMP.2012.1.2-3','Nanomedicine is the application of nanotechnology to health. An EU-funded project is adding to the research being conducted in this important field.','Cultivating research in nanomedicine','2015-04-08 10:44:00.000000'),(158597,103500,'SEC-2011.1.2-1','An EU-funded research project worked to develop an urban sensor network for monitoring terrorist threats. The network combines with systems for evaluating the 3D city environment and human behaviours, and also suggests responses.','Terrorism detectors','2015-04-08 10:46:00.000000'),(158598,93571,'ENV.2009.3.1.5.1','Ten research institutes joined their efforts with the private sector to help strengthen Europe\'s resilience against floods. The initiative broke new ground by disseminating advanced knowledge on \'smart\' flood protection technologies.','High-tech solutions for flood protection','2015-04-08 11:58:00.000000'),(158599,102548,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Unlocking the secrets of ageing promises to be the key to developing therapies for many chronic and age-related diseases. The startling difference between lifespan of worker ants (2 years) and queens (up to 29 years) provided an EU-funded project with insight on the molecular basis behind senescence.','DNA housekeeping in long-lived queen ants','2015-04-08 12:05:00.000000'),(158600,94613,'FP7-PEOPLE-2009-RG','Observations indicate that most baryonic matter does not reside in galaxies, but in the intergalactic medium. EU-funded scientists looked at regions where gas outflows from galaxies meet the intergalactic medium to find the key to a number of astrophysical and cosmological questions.','Baryons at low densities','2015-04-08 12:07:00.000000'),(158601,99434,'FP7-PEOPLE-2010-IEF','When cells divide, there has to be genomic stability or chaos may follow in the wake of mistakes in the DNA structure. An EU-funded project has looked at the molecules in the specialised networks maintaining faithful replication of the chromosome.','Genetic quality control in dividing cells','2015-04-08 12:33:00.000000'),(158602,96869,'HEALTH.2010.2.1.1-2','Correct interpretation, storage and dissemination of the massive amount of genomics data currently available present many challenges. Seventeen partners from seven European countries have put the human genome into the context of human health and future personalised medicine.','Optimising genomic data','2015-04-08 12:37:00.000000'),(158603,90165,'FP7-PEOPLE-IRSES-2008','Anion transporters are a vital part of cell systems and impact on many physiological functions. A team of two American and two European institutions are investigating the dynamics of two important anion transporters.','Cell anion transporter role variation','2015-04-08 12:41:00.000000'),(158604,109542,'SME-2013-1','European small and m