ve and reparative therapies for hearing impairment (HI) that can serve as alternatives to cochlear implants.','Pre-clinical studies on hearing loss','2015-04-08 16:26:00.000000'),(158624,105361,'HEALTH.2012.2.3.2-3','Malaria continues to affect millions of people worldwide. Vaccine development has been one of the main struggles of health research globally.','A novel malaria vaccine','2015-04-08 16:29:00.000000'),(158625,104797,'KBBE.2012.2.3-02','Researchers in the EU are developing and testing an automated non-invasive scanner to rapidly measure lean content of pig carcasses and primal cuts.','Automatic system for determining lean content distribution in pig carcasses','2015-07-06 16:23:00.000000'),(158626,105213,'ENV.2012.6.5-2','An EU team is developing new industrial methods for recovering valuable materials from electronic waste. Addressing a total of 17 metals, the project has built two recycling plants, one mobile and one stationary, and testing has commenced.','Recycling electronic waste','2015-04-08 16:35:00.000000'),(158627,105359,'HEALTH.2012.3.2-2','Technology has the potential to improve clinical practice. An EU-funded project is exploring how to ensure that only high-value innovations are implemented.','Facilitating valuable health technologies in European hospitals','2015-04-08 16:47:00.000000'),(158628,102669,'JTI-CS-2011-2-ECO-01-027','The aerospace industry is committed to reducing the environmental impact of its activities. An innovative EU-funded project focused on the use of biodegradable biocomposites rather than the more commonly addressed reduction in emissions.','Sugar and jute aeroplane panels','2015-04-08 16:50:00.000000'),(158629,99437,'FP7-PEOPLE-2010-IIF','Conflict between maternal and paternal genes alters metabolic and psychological pathways in offspring. Analysis of a large Danish health database is shedding light on genetic influences from parent genes before birth.','Parent offspring gene conflict in the womb','2015-04-08 16:52:00.