lso establishing several new networks and improving Chile\'s research capacity.','Research relationships with Chile','2015-07-17 17:49:00.000000'),(165885,104887,'ENV.2012.6.1-2','Integrated assessment models (IAMs) are an essential tool for evaluating strategies that address climate change. An EU initiative is working on further advancing the state-of-the-art of IAM tools for analysing climate change mitigation policies.','Enhancing EU and global climate policy impact assessment','2015-07-17 17:45:00.000000'),(165886,106192,'HEALTH.2012.1.4-1','The availability of donor organs is exceedingly low in comparison to the demand for them. To increase utilisation of all transplantable organs, the transplant community is in urgent need of better preservation techniques.','Optimising organs for transplantation','2015-07-17 17:49:00.000000'),(165887,106350,'HEALTH.2012.3.2-1','With a shrinking working force yet increasing demand for health care by a growing elderly population, Europe needs more cost-effective health systems. To achieve this, policymakers need information on what type of community care offers the best outcomes at reasonable costs.','More independent living for the elderly','2015-07-17 18:03:00.000000'),(165889,106760,'SSH.2012.2.1-1','An EU-funded research initiative strives to reduce inequalities for young people living in deprived city districts. This can be accomplished through an expanded informational basis on which policies are designed and implemented by giving opportunities for developing aspirations and a voice to these youth.','Giving disadvantaged youth a voice','2015-07-17 18:03:00.000000'),(165890,105076,'KBBE.2012.2.4-04','In Europe alone, around 20 million people suffer from some form of food allergy. EU-funded researchers are developing evidence-based strategies to optimise food allergy management and minimise risk.','Food allergy management','2015-07-17 18:04:00.000000'),(165891,105505,'AAT.2012.3.3-4.;AAT.2012.3.4-1.','An EU group is providi