dition.','Treating mother-baby incompatibility disorders','2015-07-20 11:32:00.000000'),(165898,101035,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-ITN','Similar to fingerprints, each blood cell type has a unique molecular identity. A European consortium has joined forces to discover the identity of different haematopoietic cells and translate their findings into clinical practice.','Understanding the regulation of normal and malignant haematopoiesis','2015-07-20 11:41:00.000000'),(165899,109907,'SME-2013-1','Enjoying a buttery soft steak costs a lot. Consumers will usually pay more for a very tender piece of meat.','Economical tender beef','2015-07-20 12:29:00.000000'),(165900,102032,'FP7-PEOPLE-2010-COFUND','An EU-funded initiative which aims to  help researchers to deepen and widen their skills through increased transnational mobility and advancing research competences. The overall purpose is to boost the knowledge and innovating ability of Biscayan researchers, contributing to economic growth.','Enhancing research capacity in Bizkaia','2015-07-20 12:31:00.000000'),(165901,102031,'FP7-PEOPLE-2010-COFUND','An international postdoctoral mobility programme is working to increase the research potential and career prospects of promising young researchers. The end goal is to equip them with the means to better respond to current and future challenges in the fields of agriculture, food, nutrition and the environment.','Supporting excellence in agricultural science','2015-07-20 13:02:00.000000'),(165902,94587,'FP7-PEOPLE-2009-RG','Antibiotic and antimicrobial substances in the marine environment are of major concern since they have the potential to accelerate bacterial antibiotic resistance (AR). They could also have a negative impact on non-pathogenic bacteria responsible for sustaining vital ecosystem functions.','Antibiotic resistance in marine bacteria','2015-07-20 13:03:00.000000'),(165903,93094,'FP7-PEOPLE-ITN-2008','An EU team\'s knowledge transfer activities included training and secondment