ity and damage tolerance are needed for their certification.','Aerospace industry moves to carbon fibres','2015-07-23 17:50:00.000000'),(166053,100430,'FP7-PEOPLE-2010-IIF','A major obstacle to developing optical atomic clocks has been the difficulty of directly measuring optical frequencies. Now, scientists are opening the door to a new era of atomic clocks and high-precision spectroscopy by exploring new techniques such as femtosecond frequency combs.','Pushing the boundaries in quantum optomechanics','2015-07-23 17:51:00.000000'),(166054,100687,'FP7-PEOPLE-2010-IOF','Vaccination has long been at the forefront of tackling infectious diseases. Ongoing efforts aim to enhance the performance of existing vaccines and develop new ones against novel targets.','Advances in vaccination','2015-07-23 17:52:00.000000'),(166056,102613,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IOF','Gravity waves are ubiquitously present at the interface between two fluids and in the bulk of stratified fluids, and bear significant consequences for our understanding of atmospheric, stellar and planetary dynamics','Gravity-driven \'instructions\' in stratified fluids','2015-07-24 14:57:00.000000'),(166057,102655,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Fluctuations in atmospheric carbon dioxide (CO2) are a major component of the carbon cycle and the climate system. An EU-funded initiative investigated the past role of the Southern Ocean in influencing atmospheric CO2.','Increase in CO2 and the Southern Ocean','2015-07-27 16:24:00.000000'),(166058,102729,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IOF','EU-funded scientists have successfully synthesised coordination complexes that will act as catalysts for reducing carbon dioxide (CO2) to organic compounds to ultimately produce solar fuels.','Novel catalysts for carbon dioxide reduction','2015-07-27 16:29:00.000000'),(166059,102804,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Organic chemists have investigated several new methods to create sulfonamides, a chemical group important for manufacturing pharmaceutical drugs.','New way to make potential antibiotics discovered','2015-07-27 16:36:00.000000'),(166060,102894,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Imagine a world where recovering from damaged cartilage is no big deal for the sick and the elderly. EU-funded researchers synthesised novel hybrid biomaterials to regenerate tissue loss and function.','Next-generation hybrid biomaterials','2015-07-27 16:42:00.000000'),(166061,102969,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Research shows that rural and urban communities rate the value of farmland ecosystems two to three times higher than its estimated monetary value.','Monetising ecosystem services','2015-07-27 16:43:00.000000'),(166062,103005,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IOF','Research is examining how the processes of globalisation are redefining the nature and scope of adult education.','Blurred boundaries of adult education','2015-07-27 16:47:00.000000'),(166063,103092,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Nitrification is a key process in the cycling of nitrogen (N) in ecosystems and may be influenced by the presence of arbuscular mycorrhizal fungi (AMF) in the roots of plants. An EU-funded project tested this hypothesis.','Impact of arbuscular mycorrhiza on soils','2015-07-27 16:49:00.000000'),(166064,103093,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IOF','In the race to build a universal quantum computer, researchers not only need to be able to control complex quantum phenomena, they need to do this on a chip. Such a multi-purpose optical chip is currently being developed so that miniature circuits can soon be duplicated ï¿½ in much the same way as with modern computers.','One step closer to quantum computers','2015-07-27 16:58:00.000000'),(166065,103165,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','So far, the study of bacteria has been hampered by their small size. A European consortium aimed to revolutionise bacterial research through an innovative microscopy-based technology.','High-resolution bacterial imaging','2015-07-27 17:00:00.000000'),(166066,103174,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IOF','Water vapour fluxes are a key factor in the biosphere-atmosphere exchange of water in terrestrial ecosystems and have a major influence on the climate. However, research on the effects of climate change has traditionally centred on carbon cycling of ecosystems rather than the long-term variability of water fluxes and how these respond to extreme events.','Water vapour flux in ecosystems','2015-07-27 17:03:00.000000'),(166067,103272,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Using a technique called seismic tomography, EU-funded geoscientists have decoded information contained in seismograms to take a detailed look beneath the ground into Earth\'s lithosphere and mantle.','Seismic visions of the Earth\'s interior','2015-07-27 17:07:00.000000'),(166068,103309,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Investigating the social and spatial impacts of urban regeneration programmes in deprived and ethnically diverse neighbourhoods in southern Europe sheds light on regeneration programmes.','Uncovering the urban inequality myth','2015-07-27 17:17:00.000000'),(166069,103313,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Multi-walled carbon nanotubes (MWCNTs), some of which cause inflammation and cancer in rodents, are already present in paints, plastics and lithium batteries for portable devices. Scientists provided evidence of their mechanism of cytotoxicity.','Carbon nanomaterials akin to asbestos','2015-07-27 17:20:00.000000'),(166070,103362,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','European researchers developed a novel inï¿½vitro culture system that closely mimics the structure of the human stomach. Using this model, it is now feasible to study host-microbe interactions.','Organoids to study gastric infections','2015-07-27 17:28:00.000000'),(166071,103366,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','An EU-funded project has made an important contribution to determining a neutrino mixing parameter ï¿½ theta13 ï¿½ that is one of the last unknown fundamental parameters in the standard model.','High-precision neutrino measurements','2015-07-27 17:31:00.000000'),(166072,103395,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','There are major differences in approaches to otherness between and within European nations. EU-funded research has supported further work on a political philosophy related to welcoming the \'other\'.','Calling for a more hospitable Europe','2015-07-27 17:34:00.000000'),(166073,103483,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Understanding how cells receive signals from the outside and translate them into cellular responses is central to the field of biology and medicine.','The molecular language of cells','2015-07-27 17:39:00.000000'),(166074,103495,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IIF','Nanomaterials are famous for their unique properties that differ from those of bulk quantities of the same stuff. Now, bulk structures made from nanomaterials are the next generation and EU-funded scientists are paving the way.','In situ formation of nanotubes by tunnelling','2015-07-27 17:40:00.000000'),(166075,103588,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Improving technological support through a user-centred approach can help the older population live fuller and more independent lives.','Technology for older people to live more independently','2015-07-27 17:42:00.000000'),(166076,103623,'JTI-CS-2011-3-ECO-01-036','Growth of microorganisms in aircraft fuel tanks can block the flow of fuel and cause corrosion, affecting both safety and maintenance costs. Novel antimicrobial coatings could solve the problem simply and effectively.','Eliminating fungus in aircraft fuel tanks','2015-07-27 17:57:00.000000'),(166077,103797,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IOF','An EU-funded project is exploiting innovative routes that rely on nanotechnology to further develop the potential of third-generation photovoltaics. Exciton harvesting is a fundamental parameter for efficient operation of such photovoltaic devices.','Boosting efficiency of excitonic solar cells','2015-07-28 17:51:00.000000'),(166078,103826,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Acute and chronic lung injury is a major cause of morbidity and mortality worldwide. Understanding and modelling the mechanisms of lung tissue repair are needed to find ways to r