mprove the resolution and diversify the functionality of AFM systems, new cantilevers are being pioneered, which promise to significantly enhance their capabilities.','Fast all-electric detection in atomic force microscopy','2015-08-05 15:56:00.000000'),(169411,110282,'SME-2013-1','Commercial buildings consume about 40ï¿½% of all the energy produced in Europe. An EU initiative is working on a system for space heating of non-residential buildings that is expected to deliver substantial energy savings.','Making commercial buildings more energy efficient','2015-08-05 15:57:00.000000'),(169412,106449,'Fission-2012-1.1.2','It is in the interests of all European countries that research and development (R&D) continues to address nuclear waste management. The key to enhancing cooperation is the Implementing Geological Disposal of Radioactive Waste Technology Platform (IGD-TP) supported by the EU.','Radioactive waste management: A common issue','2015-08-05 15:58:00.000000'),(169413,106492,'JTI-CS-2012-1-GRA-01-043','A new health management solution acts as a \'virtual\' maintenance team, determining the status of an aircraft and its subsystems to supply actionable information and help aircraft operators.','Wireless sensing for aircraft health monitoring','2015-08-05 15:59:00.000000'),(169414,106839,'KBBE.2012.3.6-01','An EU project is promoting European complementary systems biology (SB) projects. Their focus is on translational SB with applications in industry.','Expanding the systems biology network','2015-08-05 16:00:00.000000'),(169415,109169,'JTI-CS-2012-3-SAGE-06-002','3D printing is set to take off in aircraft combustor parts of thanks to an EU-funded project that is developing a next-generation laser additive manufacturing machine.','Low-cost manufacturing of lean-burn engine parts','2015-08-05 16:01:00.000000'),(169416,106012,'ENERGY.2012.7.1.1','Smart grids implement two-way communication, sensors and intelligent control to improve the efficiency, sustainability an