ALTH.2012.4.1-4','An EU team has contributed to efforts aimed at reducing health care costs by helping to prevent mental decline in elderly citizens. To that group, the project also communicated the benefits of EU health research via a collaborative process and by engaging media such as films.','Promoting brain health','2015-10-15 15:45:00.000000'),(169453,102590,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Imaging mass spectrometry (MS) tools are like chemical microscopes for investigating the spatial distribution of molecules at surfaces. Scientists have drastically expanded capabilities, paving the way to clinical applications.','Label-free mapping of biomolecules in brain tissue','2015-08-14 17:41:00.000000'),(169454,103883,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','An EU study developed techniques for improving statistical awareness among children. The method involves allowing classroom talk combined with visualisation software, and has led to improved test score performance.','Probability theory for youngsters','2015-08-14 17:53:00.000000'),(169455,102585,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Birdsong exhibits phonological syntax in which sounds are put together in an organised syntactic structure that produces meaning. The first use of electrodes to study sequence rule learning in non-human animals has shed light on neural mechanisms.','Neural responses of birds to sound sequences','2015-08-14 17:54:00.000000'),(169456,95731,'FP7-PEOPLE-2009-RG','Two main drivers of global innovation and economic growth are the semiconductor/integrated chip (IC) market and renewable energy. Deeper understanding of the mechanisms of charge transport in advanced materials could advance both fields substantially.','Charge transport in transition metal oxides','2015-08-14 18:02:00.000000'),(169457,103972,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Several neurodegenerative disorders, including Parkinson\'s disease, are associated with dysfunctions of the dopamine system. Understanding dopamine synthesis regulation will facilitate exploration of new therapeutic options for such diseases, affecting millions of people worldwide.','Neurotransmitters and neurodegenerative diseases','2015-08-14 18:02:00.000000'),(169458,102555,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','While the positive contributions of nanotechnology are easy to see, the potentially negative ones are not, and suitable tests to quantify them are lacking. A study of nanoparticle (NP) effects on microbes highlighted the difficulties.','Towards realistic ecotoxicity evaluation of nanoparticles','2015-08-19 17:11:00.000000'),(169459,101369,'HEALTH 2011.4.1-3','EU-LAC Health project is working towards a joint initiative between the European Union (EU) and the Community of Latin America and the Caribbean (CELAC) countries to enhance and coordinate the scientific and technological collaboration between the two regions in the area of health research and innovation.','Paving the way for cooperative health research and innovation','2015-08-19 17:12:00.000000'),(169460,109286,'NMP.2013.4.0-6','Safe use and further development of the European transportation, production and energy infrastructures is facing difficulties related to their advanced age. The SAFELIFE--X project proposes new methods, aligned strategic research agenda and a new EN standard helping to cope better with these difficulties.','Safe life extension management of aged infrastructures networks and industrial plants','2015-08-19 18:00:00.000000'),(169461,111098,'JTI-CS-2012-1-GRA-03-009','For most of aeronautics history, moveable aircraft systems like landing gear and brakes have used hydraulic fluids to do their work. The new trend is towards all-electric aircraft, and rudder control is about to become the next beneficiary.','All-electric support of aircraft guidance','2015-08-19 18:00:00.000000'),(169462,106999,'JTI-CS-2011-3-SGO-02-037','Existent power modules relying on silicon electronics do not allow for drastic weight and volume reductions as more-electric aircraft call for. EU-funded scientists seek to gain a better view of the design criteria of next-generation power converters through a technical feasibility study.','Studying aircraft power electronics of the future','2015-08-19 18:09:00.000000');
INSERT INTO `brief` VALUES (169463,102808,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Bacteria live in high-density colonies where they inevitably interact with their neighbours. An EU-funded project has used a computer model to predict the evolution of social interactions between five types of bacteria that treat industrial waste.','Microbial social interactions','2015-08-19 18:10:00.000000'),(169464,185720,'SP1-JTI-FCH.2013.1.5','Understanding the requirements for hydrogen fuel quality and quality assurance for road vehicles is the key to decreasing the cost of hydrogen for the large-scale commercialisation of fuel cell road vehicles.','Assessing the risk of hydrogen fuel contamination','2015-08-20 09:42:00.000000'),(169465,108386,'SME-2012-3','Windows are a major source of heat loss from buildings. To address this problem, a European consortium of manufacturers and suppliers are developing a high-performance self-regulating window.','Hi-tech windows save energy','2015-08-20 09:42:00.000000'),(169466,105130,'FP7-PEOPLE-2012-IRSES','Researchers from around the world are joining forces to promote sustainable development through clean energy technologies.','International collaboration on clean energy','2015-08-20 09:52:00.000000'),(169467,103699,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Scientists have investigated how the roots of crops respond to periods of flooding in order to ensure good harvests.','The impact of flooding on plant roots','2015-08-20 09:53:00.000000'),(169468,108715,'NMP.2013.4.0-4','An open team of researchers, industry representatives and other stakeholders is focusing on four nanotechnology value chains to develop a clear plan for their implementation. Success will have far-reaching impact on European and global challenges.','Fast-forward for nanotechnology','2015-09-10 12:51:00.000000'),(169469,111176,'SME-2013-1','Europe accounts for one third of global natural stone production and has the highest per capita consumption in the world. An EU initiative is tackling technological challenges that threaten the stone industry\'s competitiveness.','Ancient artistic stone processing meets modern technology','2015-08-20 10:41:00.000000'),(169470,105461,'FP7-PEOPLE-2012-IRSES','A staff exchange programme is strengthening international ties and developing biosensors for diseases affecting livestock. It will also prepare a new generation of scientists to address other applications of fibre optic biosensors.','Nanotechnology to detect livestock diseases','2015-08-20 10:48:00.000000'),(169471,110084,'SME-2013-1','Close to 6 million tonnes of used tyres have been illegally dumped or landfilled. An innovative and cost-effective recycling process that yields high-end products will increase the competitiveness of the tyre reclamation industry and encourage recycling.','Energy-efficient rubber pyrolysis and sulphur removal','2015-08-20 10:49:00.000000'),(169472,107430,'FP7-PEOPLE-2012-IEF','Gene therapy is an alternative therapeutic approach for genetic disorders, which promises to replace the missing protein by introducing the wild-type gene. An EU-funded study set out to develop a gene therapy approach for haemophilia.','Gene therapy for haemophilia','2015-08-20 15:26:00.000000'),(169473,109640,'FP7-PEOPLE-2012-IEF','Smart meters deliver substantial energy and cost savings, but also raise privacy concerns. An EU initiative has created a system that tackles data protection, privacy and security issues voiced by consumers.','Protecting personal data in innovative energy management','2015-08-20 15:27:00.000000'),(169474,109925,'SME-2013-1','A green technology that uses reed beds to treat wastewater is receiving a major boost thanks to an EU initiative extending the system\'s working life.','Improving reed bed water treatment','2015-08-20 15:45:00.000000'),(169475,105067,'KBBE.2012.3.4-02','The world generates garbage, municipal solid waste (MSW) on a massive scale, and landfilling it creates long-term environmental and economic pressures. Cost-effective and efficient technology to turn it into biodegradable biopolymers is around the corner.','From garbage to biopolymers in one step','2015-08-20 15:46:00.000000'),(169476,104966,'FP7-PEOPLE-2012-IRSES','An EU initiative is improving technologies and biological tools for waste conversion into high-added value products using environmentally friendly methods. These products include ligno-cellulolytic enzymes, fuel ethanol (EtOH), polylactic acid (PLA) and polyhydroxyalkanoates (PHAs).','Microbes and enzymes yielding new products from waste','2015-08-20 15:59:00.000000'),(169477,110624,'SME-2013-1','EU-funded researchers are developing a new woodchip feeding system for small-scale heating plants that should significantly reduce emissions.','New system for biomass heating','2015-08-20 16:00:00.000000'),(169478,106518,'JTI-CS-2012-1-SFWA-01-042','Keeping aircraft in flight for hours over hundreds of thousands of miles burns a tremendous amount of fuel, creating a significant amount of emissions. Novel active flow control solutions to ensure wings remain aerodynamically sound will have major benefits.','Pulsed air valves improve aerodynamic flow over airplane wings','2015-08-20 16:13:00.000000'),(169479,105103,'KBBE.2012.2.2-01','Enriching commonly consumed foods with bioactive ingredients may help promote health and curb disease risk. To support such product innovation, PATHWAY-27 will define best practice from food conception to health impact testing and claims dossiers.','Bioactive-enriched foods for better health','2015-08-20 16:13:00.000000'),(169480,108538,'INFRA-2012-1.1.1.','The European Commission has set ambitious targets to fight poverty, reduce inequality, and create more and better jobs. An EU initiative aims to facilitate and improve comparative research in order to boost inclusive growth.','Towards social inclusion in Europe','2015-08-20 16:48:00.000000'),(169481,110834,'SME-2013-1','An EU team is developing a new material for road markings. The sprayable cement and polymer-latex compound has numerous superior properties, especially durability, meaning improved visibility and road safety.','Tougher, safer road marking','2015-08-20 16:49:00.000000'),(169482,106403,'FP7-PEOPLE-2012-IRSES','The Southern Ocean plays a major role in controlling carbon dioxide (CO2) concentrations in the atmosphere. An EU-funded project is therefore investigating the role of the Southern Ocean in global carbon cycling.','EU-South Africa carbon cycle research','2015-08-20 16:58:00.000000'),(169483,110941,'SME-2013-1','Disposal of sludge in Europe has become an increasingly pressing issue. An EU-funded research consortium is working on an economically and environmentally sound solution.','Biochar for safe sewage sludge disposal','2015-08-20 16:59:00.000000'),(169484,103787,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','A comparative and in-depth analysis of the micro-dynamics of violence during and after militant insurgencies contributes to understanding trajectories and outcomes of violent conflict.','Patterns of transformation in violent conflict','2015-08-20 17:26:00.000000'),(169485,96214,'FP7-PEOPLE-2009-RG','A closer look at contact theory reveals challenges associated with the application of the theory, and ways in which these challenges can be overcome to advance justice and equality.','Social change through contact','2015-08-20 17:27:00.000000'),(169486,103863,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Why are art and death associated in Neolithic tombs? Moreover, how was art used to create appropriate spaces appropriate for those who had passed away?','Studying European Neolithic rock art','2015-08-20 17:41:00.000000'),(169487,103775,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Researchers examined the quality and effects of EU criminal intelligence. Europe is involved in the practice, but efforts are fragmented and uncooperative; such work may breach presumptions of innocence and is not recommended as trial evidence.','Assessing EU criminal intelligence','2015-08-20 17:41:00.000000'),(169488,106941,'NMP.2012.1.4-3','Harnessing the Sun\'s unlimited (for all practical purposes) energy supply is one of the most promising alternatives to combustion of fossil fuels. Improved characterisation of coatings for concentrating solar power (CSP) systems will speed development.','From nano-scale properties to large-scale function','2015-08-20 17:47:00.000000'),(169489,95897,'FP7-PEOPLE-2009-RG','Understanding the function of a single protein most often necessitates the delineation of its molecular structure.','The structure of molecular chaperones','2015-08-20 17:48:00.000000'),(169490,99573,'FP7-PEOPLE-2010-IEF','EU-funded researchers focused on interpretation and evaluation of Sicilian inscriptions under the Roman Empire.','Interpreting ancient Sicilian inscriptions','2015-08-20 17:53:00.000000'),(169491,101529,'INCO.2011-6.2','As cross-border markets grow and global concerns increase, there is an urgent need to facilitate knowledge sharing between societies. To achieve sharing and consumption of knowledge, however, we need to overcome cultural diversity and language barriers.','Breaking the barriers to knowledge sharing','2015-08-20 17:53:00.000000'),(169492,104389,'KBBE.2012.3.2-02','Biotechnologists are tapping the vast potential of ocean-dwelling microorganisms to provide new products.','New methods for growing marine microbes','2015-08-25 15:29:00.000000'),(169493,102389,'FP7-PEOPLE-2009-RG','The emergence of new production and information technologies have spurred competition and increased consumer demand, resulting in dwindling product life cycles and unstable markets. An EU initiative is devising solutions to effectively manage supply chains.','Optimising supply chains','2015-08-25 15:38:00.000000'),(169494,106805,'SME-2012-1','The average car uses approximately 40 to 50 square metres of fabric, and not only in its upholstery. Textile fibres are used in seat belts, interior panels, sandwich panels and more, so switching to biopolymers from polyester will make cars much greener.','Biodegradable fabrics for cars','2015-08-25 15:39:00.000000'),(169495,107917,'FP7-PEOPLE-2012-IEF','As associations to money change, along with its relationship to time and freedom, the deterring abilities and perceived proportionality of penal fines to crime change as well.','The new meaning of penal fines','2015-08-25 16:11:00.000000'),(169496,110086,'SME-2013-1','Breast cancer constitutes the most frequent form of cancer in women. Efforts to improve diagnostic precision rely on novel imaging methods.','Speeding-up breast cancer diagnosis','2015-08-25 16:38:00.000000'),(169497,105703,'HEALTH.2012.3.2-2','Current health technology assessment (HTA) is not adequate for complex technologies. Therefore the project develops guidances for comprehensive, patient-centred, integrative health technology assessments of complex technologies.','Guidance for patient-centred, integrative health technology assessments of complex technologies','2015-08-25 16:39:00.000000'),(169498,105949,'NMP.2012.4.0-1','Big solar panels in buildings may soon become a thing of the past. An EU-funded project seeks to develop new solar technologies for tapping the Sun\'s bountiful energy directly through building construction materials themselves.','New technology for customised solar modules','2015-08-25 16:47:00.000000'),(169499,106326,'NMP.2012.4.0-1','EU funding is giving designers the opportunity to radically change the look and feel of products, unlocking wholly new modes of product-user interaction. Wearable sports devices, rehabilitation aids and even car interiors are just some of the markets that stand to benefit from the new ï¿½light touch materialsï¿½ developed in this project.','Smart products with a sense of touch','2015-09-10 12:51:00.000000'),(169500,105655,'FoF.NMP.2012-7','Strong and lightweight metal and metal alloy components are cornerstones of products in the automotive, wind power and construction sectors. Novel nano-reinforcements and improved casting technologies will enhance product performance and industry sustainability.','Improved alloys for demanding applications','2015-08-25 16:53:00.000000'),(169501,108865,'JTI-CS-2012-1-SGO-03-017','An EU team developed an on-board controller for optimising aircraft Continuous Descent Approach (CDA) to airports. The system smoothes descent by minimising the use of engines and brakes, also considering external factors such as wind.','Efficient aircraft landings','2015-08-25 16:55:00.000000'),(169502,98143,'NMP-2009-4.0-5','Plastics and composites have improved products and applications in numerous industries, from automotive to biomedical to consumer electronics. Smart composite mould technology will advance the state of the art and expand markets for manufacturers.','Composite moulds for composite products','2015-08-26 16:13:00.000000'),(169503,108670,'SiS.2012.1.3.3-1','A network of stakeholders is adopting and diffusing a common understanding in responsible research and innovation (RRI) between different actors in Europe and internationally. The action ultimately targets support for nesting RRI into products and services from the get-go (so-called efficient RRI by design).','A global approach to responsible research and innovation','2015-08-26 16:50:00.000000'),(169504,99774,'NMP-FP7-2010-4.0-7','Nanomaterials have very large surface areas compared to their volumes, thus, providing lots of interface. This creates exotic properties for new materials that need to be carefully assessed for reactions with biological systems.','Transnational research on nanotoxicity','2015-08-26 17:24:00.000000'),(169505,106570,'SPA.2012.1.3-01','An EU project is developing new software and hardware to improve European and global monitoring of greenhouse gas (GHG) concentrations and fluxes.','Improved greenhouse gas monitoring','2015-08-26 17:36:00.000000'),(169506,110092,'SME-2013-3','Human and bovine tuberculosis (TB) are global health problems of immense social and economic importance. Urgently needed diagnostic methods capable of differentiating between active and latent infections are under development.','Advancing diagnostics for tuberculosis','2015-08-26 17:37:00.000000'),(169507,106207,'NMP.2012.1.3-2','The speed with which products incorporating nanomaterials are entering the market is tremendous, and many, many more are in the pipeline. High-throughput computational tools will soon be able to predict potential toxicity.','Computer \'assays\' to predict nanoparticle toxicity','2015-08-26 17:49:00.000000'),(169508,106539,'NMP.2012.2.1-2','EU-funded scientists are developing novel routes to value-added chemicals that will reduce both carbon dioxide (CO2) emissions and the production cost of biodiesel.','Glycerol + CO2 = useful chemicals','2015-08-27 09:36:00.000000'),(169509,108902,'JTI-CS-2012-2-ECO-01-054','Aluminium (Al) is a lightweight metal used to make millions of products supporting the global economy. New eco-friendly technologies to increase corrosion resistance without the use of carcinogens will help industry stay in business sustainably.','Green corrosion resistance for aluminium','2015-08-27 09:40:00.000000'),(169510,104997,'REGPOT-2012-2013-1','Greece\'s renowned National Center for Scientific Research \'Demokritos\' (NCSRD) conducts world-class basic and applied research for advancing scientific knowledge and promoting technological development in designated areas of national socioeconomic interest. An EU initiative is helping to boost the Center\'s capacity in environment- and climate-related research.','Enhancing environmental and climate research in Greece','2015-08-27 09:40:00.000000'),(169511,102873,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IOF','Nature is a treasure trove of interesting molecules that inspire new products and processes. EU-funded scientists made important progress towards selectively synthesising complex natural molecules that are gaining increasing attention.','Novel building blocks of natural molecules','2015-08-27 09:42:00.000000'),(169512,110519,'SME-2013-1','The versatile hemp plant has found a use in the food and health product industries by providing a source of dietary additives that improve gut health.','Hemp for health','2015-08-27 09:42:00.000000'),(169513,106382,'NMP.2012.2.1-1','Composite or hybrid materials in which two or more individual materials are joined together can produce high-performance lightweight structures not possible with either material alone. Scientists are exploiting carbon nanotubes at the joint to enhance bond characteristics.','Nanotechnology builds strong joints','2015-08-27 09:48:00.000000'),(169514,111117,'JTI-CS-2013-1-GRC-05-008','EU-funded scientists are working to minimise helicopter noise emissions during airport approach and take-off. Real-time noise computation is a promising line of research that an EU-funded project is pursuing.','Innovative system for quieter helicopter','2015-08-27 09:49:00.000000'),(169515,108716,'NMP.2013.4.0-5','The Eastern Partnership (EaP) is the EU\'s leading policy initiative to support development in six countries in Eastern Europe and the South Caucasus. A new scientific component will foster nanotechnology and materials science entrepreneurship.','Fostering scientific development in Eastern Partnership countries','2015-08-27 09:56:00.000000'),(169516,106701,'NMP.2012.2.1-1','An EU-funded project focuses on developing an innovative system for joining metals and plastics or plastic composites together using laser technology. Project results should have important implications for automakers seeking to lower emissions and improve fuel consumption.','Laser technique for bonding plastic to metal','2015-08-27 10:11:00.000000'),(169517,110344,'SME-2013-1','Primary hyperoxaluria (PH) is a rare and devastating disease resulting in renal failure and death at a young age. An EU consortium is developing a drug product based on Oxalobacter formigenes, to promote enteric elimination of oxalate through the gut and thereby protect the kidneys.','New therapy for primary hyperoxaluria','2015-08-27 10:11:00.000000'),(169518,111085,'SME-2013-1','A new wireless monitoring sensor system with a novel biosensor unit that autonomously monitors and controls the clean-up of contaminated sites will save time, money and increase the efficiency of bioremediation','Microbes that monitor bioremediation','2015-08-27 11:09:00.000000'),(169519,106864,'NMP.2012.2.1-1','Polymer-based composites provide higher strength, lower weight, and better corrosion and impact resistance compared to conventional metal materials. Novel thermal joining processes to bond them with metals will expand applications and benefits.','Joining polymers and metals','2015-08-27 11:10:00.000000'),(169520,110982,'SME-2013-1','Most advanced display technology exploits indium tin oxide (ITO) films that are facing resource scarcity and rising costs. Breakthrough technology that is cost effective, eco-friendly and supports flexible displays will put the EU in a world leadership position.','European-made low-cost flexible displays','2015-08-27 12:06:00.000000'),(169521,105378,'FP7-PEOPLE-2012-IRSES','The beauty of mathematics even for non-mathematicians lies in its ability to explain the world around us, to make the seemingly abstract more concrete. Advances in an important field of mathematics are providing a window on physical and biological systems.','Dynamical systems theory and applications','2015-08-27 12:06:00.000000'),(169522,111077,'SME-2013-2','A real-time environmental and climate monitoring system to be installed in rice farmers\' fields is being developed to help manage devastating fungal diseases like rice blast.','Monitoring environmental parameters for rice blast prediction','2015-08-28 09:41:00.000000'),(169523,104661,'FP7-PEOPLE-2012-ITN','Cancer diagnosis and monitoring would be easier if we could measure certain parameters associated with disease stage. In this respect, biomarkers in body fluids offer a significant advantage.','Biomarkers for bladder cancer','2015-08-28 10:51:00.000000'),(169524,105333,'KBBE.2012.1.1-02','Livestock farms are increasing in size more than ever before, but the number of farmers that care of the farm animals has not grown proportionately. An EU initiative aims to introduce technology that provides automatic round-the-clock monitoring of animals to mitigate the negative socioeconomic and environmental consequences while improving animal health and welfare.','Exploiting the potential of precision livestock farming','2015-08-28 11:01:00.000000'),(169525,104678,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Understanding how glacier sliding and iceberg calving contribute to loss in ice sheet models can improve predictions of global sea-level changes. This is hampered by the inaccessibility of a glacier\'s base and its calving front.','Studying the dynamics of glacial ice','2015-08-28 11:35:00.000000'),(169526,110779,'AAT.2012.6.3-1.','An EU-funded project is investigating new concepts for engine nacelles and their implementation in next-generation propulsion systems that promise to increase engine performance and decrease acoustic emissions.','Novel engine nacelles that deform','2015-08-28 12:08:00.000000'),(169527,104657,'FP7-PEOPLE-2012-ITN','EU funding has provided an opportunity for young researchers to spend time studying cloud formation at the European Organization for Nuclear Research (CERN) in Switzerland.','Cloud watching at microscopic scale','2015-08-28 12:14:00.000000'),(169528,103909,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Understanding how cancer cells migrate and become metastatic is central to designing therapies for aggressive tumours.','Regulation of cell architecture','2015-08-28 12:16:00.000000'),(169529,108647,'INFRA-2012-1.1.15.','Scientists use ever-more sophisticated numerical models to understand the mechanisms that shape Earth\'s climate and predict how it is likely to evolve. An EU-funded project is boosting Europe\'s contribution to this on-going international research effort and facilitates the distribution and exploitation of model data.','Fostering understanding and prediction of climate change','2015-08-28 12:17:00.000000'),(169530,105363,'HEALTH.2012.2.1.1-1-B','European researchers are using high-throughput technologies to delineate the mechanisms and explore novel therapeutic approaches for rare kidney diseases. The ultimate goal is to improve the dismal prognosis of patient with these disorders.','Understanding rare kidney diseases','2015-08-28 12:43:00.000000'),(169531,103460,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','A better understanding of the ways in which language and grammar encode logical relations is possible via cross-fertilisation between disciplines, providing new advances in the fields of linguistics and philosophy.','The interlocking of logic and meaning in language','2015-08-28 13:01:00.000000'),(169532,102810,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Europe\'s native fauna is under threat from invasive species populating new habitats. One of the most successful is the raccoon dog (Nyctereutes procyonoides), which is able to rapidly adapt and severely affect the biodiversity of native species.','Combating the spread of invasive species','2015-08-28 15:02:00.000000'),(169533,109458,'HEALTH.2013.1.3-1','European scientists are working to develop a computational model to predict drug-associated toxicity.','Modelling organ system toxicity','2015-08-28 15:38:00.000000'),(169534,108067,'FP7-PEOPLE-2012-IEF','Understanding how cells respond to extracellular signals is central to biomedical research. European scientists set out to dissect the initial events of receptor-mediated signalling.','Dissecting cell transduction','2015-08-28 15:41:00.000000'),(169535,104209,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IIF','Cancer stem cells constitute a relatively new discovery with great clinical implications. Targeting this cell population may be all that is needed to eradicate the tumour.','Targeting cancer stem cells','2015-08-28 16:06:00.000000'),(169536,103973,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IOF','A transcontinental research project is investigating the factors that allowed an aggressive North American plant species to successfully invade Europe.','Learning how plants invade','2015-08-28 17:46:00.000000'),(169537,103215,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Sandwich structures made of composite faces between which a foam or honeycomb core is sandwiched are a winning low weight-high strength partnership. New piezoelectric feedback control will induce shape morphing to prevent a common impact issue.','Better sandwich structures for the transport sector','2015-08-28 17:47:00.000000'),(169538,107835,'FP7-PEOPLE-2012-IIF','Not much is known about the interaction between requirements engineering (RE) and systems architecting (SA), widely considered the two most important phases of the software development life cycle. An EU initiative has examined RE and SA processes to provide insight and improve operations and technology.','Examining human and technical impact on software development','2015-08-28 17:53:00.000000'),(169539,105265,'FP7-PEOPLE-2012-ITN','An EU-funded team is providing training to young researchers in the field of soft matter at aqueous interfaces. The programme, which is designed to offer scientific and transferable skills training, consists of training by research in the fellowsï¿½ home institutions, a ramified system of secondments and exchanges as well as of a series of 10 special training events.','Training in soft matter science','2015-08-28 17:54:00.000000'),(169540,103886,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Antimicrobial resistance (AR) is currently responsible for 15 times as many deaths caused by AIDS every year. EU researchers are investigating one of the microbes\' genetic vehicles of resistance, the integron.','Knowledge-based approach to tackle antimicrobial resistance','2015-08-28 18:17:00.000000'),(169541,103859,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IOF','An EU project is investigating how plants in different ecosystems affect nitrogen cycling in the soil of that ecosystem.','How plants influence the nitrogen cycle','2015-08-28 18:17:00.000000'),(169542,104717,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IEF','Obesity has become a major health issue, and the EU has prioritised the design of healthier foods to control the phenomenon.','Optimising fat digestion','2015-09-01 09:49:00.000000'),(169543,108221,'FP7-PEOPLE-2012-IOF','EU-funded research has investigated evolution of rat morphology in three islands in the Indo-Pacific archipelagos. Using a unique ecomorphological data set, the researchers have uncovered new patterns of evolution and ecology.','Evolution of Indo-Pacific rats','2015-09-01 10:40:00.000000'),(169544,106249,'INFRA-2012-1.1.4.','The mouse is similar to humans in terms of development, physiology and its underlying genome. European researchers are developing mouse mutant models to investigate genes implicated in the whole spectrum of human disease.','Mouse models contributing to understanding human health and disease','2015-09-01 10:58:00.000000'),(169545,103035,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IOF','The quantum nature of nitrogen-vacancy centres in diamond is being widely explored for use in quantum information processing. Another possible application is to harness their quantum properties to detect very small magnetic fields.','Quantum sensing using single spins','2015-09-01 11:01:00.000000'),(169546,102868,'FP7-PEOPLE-2011-IIF','Using the Baryon Oscillation Spectroscopic Survey (BOSS), astronomers from Europe and the United States tracked hundreds of thousands of quasars. A pair of these studies provided a rare glimpse into the structure of the young Universe.','Discovering the very early Universe','2015-09-01 11:10:00.000000'),(169547,105266,'FP7-PEOPLE-2012-ITN','There is growing interest in the potential and power of immersive technology for scheduled and emergency maintenance in extreme environments such as nuclear installations. An EU initiative is exploring the use of virtual reality (VR) and augmented reality (AR) ï¿½ the blending of virtual reality and real life ï¿½ for personnel safety systems.','Novel immersive technology for work in dangerous areas','2015-09-01 11:12:00.000000'),(169548,111005,'SME-2013-1','Despite stringent safety and hygiene standards, meat and poultry products can be vehicles for food-borne illnesses. A nine-member EU-funded consortium is developing a new decontamination process for packed meats to ensure meat safety without compromising taste and nutritional content.','Longer life for packaged meat','2015-09-01 11:17:00.000000'),(169558,96807,'FP7-PEOPLE-2009-RG','An EU team considered the design of negotiation software systems that interact with humans. Researchers used game theory to model negotiation behaviour, including cultural differences, yielding a system at least as proficient as human negotiators.','Model negotiations','2015-09-01 17:36:00.000000'),(169561,96761,'FP7-PEOPLE-2009-RG','Researchers are harnessing the vast genetic resources of Europe\'s countless microbes to produce energy from renewable biological sources.','Microbial power','2015-09-01 17:41:00.000000'),(169563,95368,'FP7-PEOPLE-2009-RG','An EU team modelled factors affecting the life cycle of mobile phones. Utilising Israeli householder data, the study examined the linked economic and environmental effects of four types of industry-player companies.','Use and reuse of mobile phones','2015-09-01 17:44:00.000000'),(169569,96766,'FP7-PEOPLE-2009-RG','The wars in Afghanistan and Iraq have resulted in an increased interest in counterinsurgency. An EU initiative is exploring to what extent counterinsurgency campaigns and tactics are successful in defeating and containing insurgency while addressing its root causes.','Enhancing counterinsurgency operations','2015-09-02 10:45:00.000000'),(169577,104803,'SME-2011-3','In 2012, in the EU alone, 198 deaths were attributed to listeriosis, a condition caused by the pathogen Listeria monocytogenes. EU-funded researchers successfully developed pre-commercial prototypes to detect this microbe.','Speedy List